#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Why DDD is Having a Moment"
msgstr "Por qué la DDD está teniendo un momento"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy opened by noting that DDD seems to be experiencing renewed interest, with multiple presentation requests recently. He theorizes this resurgence relates to the rise of AI-assisted development and agentic systems, where DDD's structured approach to organizing business logic makes it easier for AI tools to understand and generate code."
msgstr "Jeremy comenzó señalando que DDD parece estar experimentando un renovado interés, con múltiples solicitudes de presentaciones recientemente. Teoriza que este resurgimiento está relacionado con el auge del desarrollo asistido por IA y los sistemas agénticos, en los que el enfoque estructurado de DDD para organizar la lógica empresarial facilita a las herramientas de IA la comprensión y la generación de código."

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Core Principles of Domain-Driven Design"
msgstr "Los principios básicos del diseño dirigido por dominios"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ubiquitous Language"
msgstr "El lenguaje omnipresente"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "One of Jeremy's favorite aspects of DDD is the emphasis on **ubiquitous language** - a shared vocabulary between developers and business stakeholders. He illustrated this with the restaurant industry example: \"86 ketchup\" means \"we're out of ketchup\" to anyone who's worked in restaurants, but is completely nonsensical to outsiders."
msgstr "Uno de los aspectos favoritos de Jeremy de DDD es el énfasis en el *lenguaje ubicuo* : un vocabulario compartido entre los desarrolladores y las partes interesadas del negocio. Lo ilustró con el ejemplo de la industria de la restauración: \"86 ketchup\" significa \"nos hemos quedado sin ketchup\" para cualquiera que haya trabajado en restaurantes, pero carece totalmente de sentido para los forasteros."

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Since every industry has its own language, DDD encourages teams to:"
msgstr "Dado que cada industria tiene su propio lenguaje, la DDD anima a los equipos a hacerlo:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Identify and document domain-specific terminology"
msgstr "Identificar y documentar la terminología específica del dominio"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Use that language consistently in code, conversations, and documentation"
msgstr "Utilice ese lenguaje de forma coherente en el código, las conversaciones y la documentación"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Refine the language iteratively with each sprint or development cycle"
msgstr "Perfeccione el lenguaje de forma iterativa con cada sprint o ciclo de desarrollo"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Domains and Subdomains"
msgstr "Dominios y subdominios"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "For the demo, Jeremy built an application for scheduling Quarkus Insights episodes, with several subdomains:"
msgstr "Para la demostración, Jeremy construyó una aplicación para programar episodios de Quarkus Insights, con varios subdominios:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Programming**: Managing episode content and scheduling"
msgstr "*Programación* : Gestión del contenido de los episodios y programación"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**People**: Managing hosts, presenters, and guests"
msgstr "*Personas* : Gestión de anfitriones, presentadores e invitados"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Engagement**: Handling viewer interactions and notifications"
msgstr "*Compromiso* : Gestión de las interacciones y notificaciones de los espectadores"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Each subdomain represents a distinct area of business concern with its own models and logic."
msgstr "Cada subdominio representa un área distinta de interés empresarial con sus propios modelos y lógica."

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Building Blocks of DDD"
msgstr "Bloques de construcción de DDD"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aggregates"
msgstr "Áridos"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Aggregates** are the core business concepts that encapsulate business rules (invariants). In Jeremy's example, the `EpisodeAggregate` serves as the root entity:"
msgstr "*Los agregados* son los conceptos empresariales centrales que encapsulan las reglas empresariales (invariantes). En el ejemplo de Jeremy, la `EpisodeAggregate` sirve como entidad raíz:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Key characteristics:"
msgstr "Características clave:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aggregates are **POJOs** with no framework dependencies"
msgstr "Los agregados son *POJOs* sin dependencias del framework"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "All business logic lives in the aggregate"
msgstr "Toda la lógica empresarial vive en el agregado"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aggregates maintain **invariants** (rules that must always be true)"
msgstr "Los agregados mantienen *invariantes* (reglas que siempre deben ser ciertas)"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "You interact with the object graph through the aggregate root"
msgstr "Se interactúa con el grafo de objetos a través de la raíz agregada"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Value Objects"
msgstr "Objetos de valor"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Value objects** encapsulate data with no identity. That is,  a value object is defined entirely by its attributes, not by some unique ID. Examples include addresses, email addresses, or in Jeremy's demo, episode titles:"
msgstr "Los *objetos de valor* encapsulan datos sin identidad. Es decir, un objeto de valor se define enteramente por sus atributos, no por algún ID único. Algunos ejemplos son las direcciones, las direcciones de correo electrónico o, en la demostración de Jeremy, los títulos de los episodios:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Value objects enable validation at creation time and make the domain model more expressive."
msgstr "Los objetos de valor permiten la validación en el momento de la creación y hacen que el modelo de dominio sea más expresivo."

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Domain Events"
msgstr "Eventos del dominio"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Domain events** represent facts that the business cares about:"
msgstr "*Los eventos de dominio* representan hechos que interesan a la empresa:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Events are:"
msgstr "Los eventos son:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Statements of fact (they have occurred)"
msgstr "Declaraciones de hechos (se han producido)"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Immutable"
msgstr "Inmutable"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Can be replayed"
msgstr "Puede reproducirse"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Enable event-driven architecture"
msgstr "Habilitar la arquitectura basada en eventos"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Unlike **commands** (which can be rejected), events represent things that have already happened."
msgstr "A diferencia de *las órdenes* (que pueden rechazarse), los eventos representan cosas que ya han sucedido."

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hexagonal Architecture"
msgstr "Arquitectura hexagonal"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Layered Approach"
msgstr "El enfoque por capas"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy demonstrated how to structure a DDD application using hexagonal architecture:"
msgstr "Jeremy demostró cómo estructurar una aplicación DDD utilizando una arquitectura hexagonal:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"**Infrastructure Layer (Adapters)**:\n"
"- REST endpoints (incoming port)\n"
"- Database repositories (outgoing port)\n"
"- Message brokers (outgoing port)\n"
"- DTOs for wire format"
msgstr "*Capa de infraestructura (adaptadores)* : - Puntos finales REST (puerto de entrada) - Repositorios de bases de datos (puerto de salida) - Corredores de mensajes (puerto de salida) - DTOs para formato alámbrico"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"**Application Layer**:\n"
"- Application services that orchestrate business logic\n"
"- Command handlers\n"
"- Domain services for logic that doesn't fit in aggregates"
msgstr "*Capa de aplicación* : - Servicios de aplicación que orquestan la lógica empresarial - Manejadores de comandos - Servicios de dominio para la lógica que no cabe en los agregados"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"**Domain Layer**:\n"
"- Aggregates\n"
"- Value objects\n"
"- Domain events\n"
"- Repository interfaces (not implementations)"
msgstr "*Capa de* dominio: - Agregados - Objetos de valor - Eventos de dominio - Interfaces de repositorio (no implementaciones)"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Application Services"
msgstr "Servicios de aplicación"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Application services orchestrate the workflow:"
msgstr "Los servicios de aplicación orquestan el flujo de trabajo:"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Separating Concerns"
msgstr "Separar las preocupaciones"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "A critical aspect of hexagonal architecture is keeping the domain pure:"
msgstr "Un aspecto crítico de la arquitectura hexagonal es mantener el dominio puro:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Aggregates** have no knowledge of persistence frameworks"
msgstr "*Los agregados* no conocen los marcos de persistencia"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Repositories** handle the translation between aggregates and entities"
msgstr "*Los repositorios* manejan la traducción entre agregados y entidades"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Mappers** convert between domain objects and database entities"
msgstr "*Los mapeadores* convierten entre objetos de dominio y entidades de base de datos"

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Trade-offs"
msgstr "Las compensaciones"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "More Code, Better Organization"
msgstr "Más código, mejor organización"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy was upfront about the main drawback: **you'll write significantly more code** with DDD compared to a simple CRUD application. The demo showed:"
msgstr "Jeremy fue franco sobre el principal inconveniente: *escribirá bastante más código* con DDD en comparación con una simple aplicación CRUD. La demo lo demostró:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Value objects for each domain concept"
msgstr "Objetos de valor para cada concepto de dominio"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Separate DTOs for REST endpoints"
msgstr "DTOs separados para puntos finales REST"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Commands for operations"
msgstr "Comandos para operaciones"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Events for notifications"
msgstr "Eventos para notificaciones"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Mappers between layers"
msgstr "Mapeadores entre capas"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Benefits"
msgstr "Los beneficios"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "However, this additional code provides substantial benefits:"
msgstr "Sin embargo, este código adicional proporciona beneficios sustanciales:"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**1. Maintainability**: When inheriting code, business logic is easy to find - it's all in the aggregates."
msgstr "*1. Mantenibilidad* : Al heredar código, la lógica empresarial es fácil de encontrar: está toda en los agregados."

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**2. Testability**: Aggregates are POJOs that can be tested with plain JUnit, no framework required."
msgstr "*2. Testabilidad* : Los agregados son POJOs que pueden probarse con JUnit simple, sin necesidad de framework."

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**3. Flexibility**: Swapping persistence frameworks (e.g., from https://hibernate.org/orm/[Hibernate] to https://firebase.google.com/[Firebase]) only requires changing the repository implementation."
msgstr "*3. Flexibilidad* : Cambiar de marco de persistencia (por ejemplo, de link:https://hibernate.org/orm/[Hibernate] a link:https://firebase.google.com/[Firebase] ) sólo requiere cambiar la implementación del repositorio."

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**4. Clear boundaries**: Logic doesn't leak across layers or get scattered in event handlers."
msgstr "*4. Límites claros* : La lógica no se filtra a través de las capas ni se dispersa en los manejadores de eventos."

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**5. AI-friendly**: The structured approach makes it easier for AI tools to understand and generate code."
msgstr "*5. Amigable con la IA* : El enfoque estructurado facilita a las herramientas de IA la comprensión y la generación de código."

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-19-quarkus-insights-248-ddd-hexagonal-architecture.adoc
#, fuzzy
